description.narrative: UNICEF achieved significant progress in KRC1. Through the routine vaccination, the percentage of districts reaching at least 80% DTP3 coverage increased from 33% in 2020 to 44% in 2021, and DTP3 coverage (children <1 year) increased from 64% to 68%. In 2021, 40% of children and 40% of pregnant women received;ARV; treatment, higher than the coverage of 28% and 31% in 2020, respectively. Although the total number of cases of COVID-19 increased from 5,356 in 2020 to 9,515 in 2021, the number of cases among health workers decreased from 371 in 2020 to 197 in 2021.; | Status:On-track | As-of Date:02/02/2022
